#Soul Strings (#1085): {X}{B} - return two target creatures from my graveyard
#to hand unless any player pays {X}. X=2, decline the pay twice -> bears and
#giant return. The pay[[{value:storedx}]] grant is the stale-X/pay[[ family:
#a broken storedx reads 0, the {0} auto-pays, and nothing ever returns.
[INIT]
firstmain
[PLAYER1]
manapool:{2}{B}
hand:soul strings
graveyard:grizzly bears,hill giant,darksteel citadel
[PLAYER2]
[DO]
soul strings
grizzly bears
hill giant
soul strings
choice 2
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
choice 1
goto firstmain
choice 1
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
[ASSERT]
FIRSTMAIN
[PLAYER1]
hand:grizzly bears,hill giant
graveyard:darksteel citadel,soul strings
[PLAYER2]
[END]
#PARKED after 3 orderings (X-menu-first, targets-first, confirm-click): the
#cast NEVER completes. Trace: card click ok, choice 2 -> ActionLayer::doReactTo
#104 (X menu answered), both graveyard target clicks land ("Clicking ON") but
#the <2>creature|mygraveyard chooser never fills -> spell never stacks, mana
#never spent. Cast-time targeting of GRAVEYARD cards appears inert (the click
#reaches the harness's getCard but the game's target chooser doesn't take it).
#Behind that wedge sit the real quarry: pay[[{value:storedx}]] in a transforms
#grant (stale-X + pay[[ family, engine round 1). Compare: dreadhorde casts
#FROM graveyard via its own ability (different path, works). REFINED
#2026-06-11: Zombify (single target=creature|mygraveyard) casts FINE - the
#wedge is specific to MULTI-target (<2>) graveyard choosers at cast time.
